      <h2 class="text-center font-semibold text-2xl py-20 lg:hidden">What's the difference between <br>Part 141 and Part 61?</h2>
      <p class="w-4/5 lg:w-3/5 grid place-items-center pb-10 p-text">Part 141 and Part 61 refer to different sections in the FAA regulations.  Part 141 is a more structured and rigorous training program that is designed for schools that are approved by the FAA to provide training under specific curricula.  Part 61, on the other hand, is a more flexible training program that allows for individualized training plans; however being less structured, students may require more hours to complete Part 61 training.</p>

